Please answer the below core-java Questions:

Q. What is programing language?
A. A programming language is a set of instructions written by a programmer
to provide instructions for the computer to perform and complete a task.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the jdk components ? define each component?
A. The JDK is the development platform for creating Java applications.
also has a private Java Virtual Machine (JVM) and a few other resources necessary
for the development of a Java Application.
The JVM consists of three distinct components:
1-Class Loader:is part of the Java Runtime Environment that dynamically loads Java classes into the Java Virtual Machine.
The Java runtime system does not need to know about files and filesystems because of classloaders.
2-Runtime Memory/Data Area: It is a part of JVM. are responsible for providing memory to store:
bytecode, intermediate results of calculations, objects, parameters, local variables, return values.
3-Execution Engine:is the central component of the JVM which communicates with different memory areas of the JVM.
Each thread of a running Java application is a distinct instance of the virtual machine’s execution engine.
reads the Java Byte code in the unit of instruction. It is like a CPU executing the machine command one by one.
