Q. If we don't have a constructor declared, what is called during the object creation?
A.we use the default constructor, without parameters.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is "this" keyword in java ?
A. The this keyword refers to the current object in a method or constructor.
The most common use of the this keyword is to eliminate the confusion between class attributes and parameters with the same name

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is "super" keyword in java? How to use it?
A. The super() function is used to give access to methods and properties of a parent or sibling class.
The super() function returns an object that represents the parent class.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is JVM stand for?
A. JVM (Java Run Environment) is a component of JRE.
It is a Java virtual machine. The compiler generates machine code for a specific scheme in other programming languages.

